pretag> s.l.</em> group and <em>B. <sd-pretag id="sdPretag738512034sm" type="organism" role="component">subtilis</sd-pretag></em> created by Mashtree (Katz et al., 2019; Ondov et al., 2016) and visualized in Microreact (Argimon et al., 2016). Rooted on <em>B. subtilis.</em> Traits for species (colored nodes), Bazinet clades and presence of <em>ena</em> are indicated on surrounding four rings in the following order from inner to outer: clade according to Bazinet 2017 (when available) (Bazinet, 2017), and presence of <sd-pretag id="sdPretag648323900sm" type="molecule" role="intervention"><em>enaA</em></sd-pretag>, <em>enaB</em> and <sd-pretag id="sdPretag223122809sm" type="geneprod" role="component"><em>enaC</em></sd-pretag>, resp. (for all three, <em>ena1</em>: teal, <em>ena2</em>: orange, different <sd-pretag id="sdPretag71191601sm" type="tissue" role="component">locus</sd-pretag>: cyan). When no homo- or ortholog was found, the ring is grey. <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1852487961sm" type="geneprod" role="component">Ena1A</sd-pretag>-C and <sd-pretag id="sdPretag195919585sm" type="geneprod" role="component">Ena2A</sd-pretag>-C are defined as present when a homologous protein of the corresponding genome has high coverage (&gt;90%) and &gt;80% and 50-65% sequence identity, respectively, with <sd-pretag id="sdPretag583536119sm" type="geneprod" role="intervention">Ena1A</sd-pretag>-C of the NMH 0095/75 strain. Interactive tree accessible at <sd-pretag id="sdPretag65599045sm" type="geneprod" role="intervention">https</sd-pretag>://microreact.org/project/vn2oWw7zM3cwejEFNoRGWA/0024f86c <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=108514"/></sd-panel></fig></article>